==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Repugn
<hw>Re*pugn"</hw> <pr>(r?-p?n")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>r⟦eacute⟧pugner</ets>, L. <ets>repugnare</ets>,
<ets>repugnatum</ets>; pref. <ets>re-</ets> + <ets>pugnare</ets> to
fight. See <er>Pugnacious</er>.]</ety> <def>To fight against; to oppose;
to resist.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Stubbornly he did <qex>repugn</qex> the truth.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Repugnable</ent>⟦br⟧
